# Define ContainerConfig struct and types

Define the core configuration struct for container settings used throughout the containerization system.

## Requirements

- Define `%ContainerConfig{}` struct with all necessary fields
- Include image, memory, CPU, network settings
- Include volume mount specifications (workspace, private, shared)
- Include isolation profile reference
- Add type specs and documentation

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `lib/pag_server/containers/container_config.ex` exists with struct definition
- [ ] Struct includes: `image`, `memory`, `cpus`, `network_mode`, `volumes`, `isolation_profile`, `env`
- [ ] All fields have proper `@type` specs
- [ ] `new/1` function with sensible defaults
- [ ] `from_workspace_config/1` to derive from workspace settings
- [ ] Module documented with examples
